\par <#/>}{\f0\fs24\lang2057 
The ultimate objective in the forthcoming multi-party elections should be to elect a government that is sensitive to the problems that affect women. <#/>It is therefore important that one understands the electoral process in a multi-party system.
\par <#/>There are three stages in multi-party elections:
\par <#/>1. }{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Party elections in which members elect party officials: }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>While individual parties may make their own election rules, the common practice is for a voter to produce a party membership card to be allowed t
o vote.
\par <#/>2. }{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Nomination of candidates for the general elections: }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 
<#/>This is the process where a party chooses a candidate to compete with candidates from other parties. <#/>It ensures that each party fields only one candidate to avoid too many candidate
s from the same party competing against each other in the general elections. <#/>Commonly, one needs only the party membership card to be allowed to nominate a candidate for that party for the elections.
\par <#/>3. }{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 The Presidential, Parliamentary and civic elections or General Elections: }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 
<#/>This is the most important stage of the electoral process. <#/>One does not need to be a member of any party to vote in general elections. <#/>One only needs to have registered as a voter and to have been issued with a vote
rs' card to vote. <#/>One also needs an identity card.
\par <h>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Why Should You Vote? }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par <#/>(a) Because it is your democratic right:
\par <#/>By voting you exercise your democratic right of electing a government or representative. <#/>Because we cannot all go to parliament where laws are made, we elect capable leaders}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 
to go to parliament to implement our wishes. <#/>Besides making laws, parliament is also the only organ which can change the constitution. <#/>The constitution is the document that guarantees righ
ts and freedoms for all citizens. <#/>Whether or not parliament will represent our interests will depend on the quality of}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 the people we choose.
\par <#/>(b) To elect a candidate of my choice:
\par <#/>Because those we elect pass laws and policies which affect all o
f us it is necessary that we should all vote to make sure that the candidate we elect will represent our views. <#/>As women, we have no choice but to favour women candidates where the opportunities arises. <#/>Indeed they are more likely to be gender sen
sitive and capable of articulating women issues in parliament.
\par <h>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Who is the Right Candidate? }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par <#/>The best candidate for women voters is the one who supports and understands women issues. <#/>This is a man or woman whose respect for women is demon
strated by his or her conduct in public and/or public life and in utterances. <#/>Those who make derogatory remarks about women or are disrespective to them are unlikely to promote women issues. <#/>In addition, the right candidate must be:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-283\li283\nowidctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent283\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>A person
 who understands issues that concern the people. <#/>The candidate must be aware of the people's problems and know how they could be solved. <#/>Such a candidate puts people and their interests first
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>A person of unquestionable integrity. <#/>The can
didate should be of good moral standing in both public and private life. <#/>This is a person not associated with such unpatriotic actions as nepotism, lying, tribalism, stealing of public funds, hypocrisy and such other behaviour.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>Sensitive to issues relating to women, children, minorities and the <-/underpriviledged>.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>A candidate who can stand for justice, equality and unity at any cost 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>A humble person. <#/>Arrogant people do not make good leaders for they do not listen to others. <#/
>They tend to be dictatorial. <#/>A democratic society is built on dialogue and only those who promote it should be elected. <#/>This dialogue must involve both sexes on an equal footing.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>A person who does not try to influence voters with gifts, mon
ey and political patronage. <#/>Candidates who offer bribes to be elected forget the wishes of the electorate as soon as they are elected because they bought their way to power.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}<#/>Respectable and respecting. <#/>This calls for a mature, educated and de
mocratic minded candidate. <#/>The candidate should have a political plan and organizational abilities needed to fight such problems as disease, poverty and ignorance.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <h>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Important }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>Voters should not be influenced by the poverty or wealth of a candidate. <#/>A poor candidate who has the above qualities is as qualified as a wealthy candidate who has the same qualities.

\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>People should not expect their individual needs e.g. <#/>school fees to be met by the leader.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <h>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 What is a Good Government? }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>A good government is one that protects not only the individual rights but also the rights of all citizens.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>Therefore, a good government is one that:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-283\li283\nowidctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent283\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 
Protects the interests of all citizens 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Promotes justice, peace, unity and equality for all irrespective of gender
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Protects the constitution
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Is not corrupt
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Understands the priority of the people
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Is beneficial to the entire society and especially to the weak
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Has a clear development programme
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Respects all political opinions
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\lang2057 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}Respects human rights
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <h> <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 How can You Help make a Good Government? }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>Every general election determines how the country will run for the next five years. <#/>You can influence this by:
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (a) Electing a government you like or by replacing one you do not want.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (b) Electing a party with the most promising policies for you and society in general
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (c) Electing a candidate you have confidence in with regard to the interests of your locality and nation.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (d) Removing and replacing a president, M.P., councillors or party found not to be responsive to
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 local and national problems.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (e) Electing men and women who can articulate on issues and initiate programmes.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 (f) Electing women leaders who understand women's issues and problems in the society.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 <h>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\f0\fs24\lang2057 <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Must You}{\b\i\f0\fs24\lang2057  }{\b\f0\fs24\lang2057 Join a Political Party?}{\f0\fs24\lang2057 </h>
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\f0\fs24\lang2057 
