er will probably give you and discuss with you questions which you are likely to be asked on particular topics. <#/>You can always consult your teacher but he will advise you not to rely on past examination papers, since examination format can change any 
time. <#/>Try to assemble as many questions as possible on a particular topic to use to test your understanding. <#/>Testing can be repeated several times in order to develop perfection.
