\par <#/> Stock control is to have a continuous check on the number and type of materials, parts and goods in your business. <#/>Good stock control is very essential for con
tinued production, and sale of goods and services. <#/>It helps you avoid shortages that could disrupt your business. <#/>It also helps you to avoid too much stocking that could tie up money unnecessarily leading to losses.
\par <#/> Your business could run out of stock and suffer due to many reasons:
\par <#/>- You have ordered too late
\par <#/>- You have forgotten to order materials, parts or goods to replace those you have used or sold.
\par <#/>- You have not found out the correct re-order level of materials and goods.
\par <#/> Running out of stock can create a lot of problems:
\par <#/>* can stop production, and this could throw you out of business.
\par <#/>* can cause dissatisfaction to your customers and they may go to your competitors, never to come back.
\par <#/>}{\b\f0\fs24 How to control stock effectively
